data.value:
HTTP FLOODING HOW-TO (USE THIS FOR SUBETA!): So what do you do? You fill in a URL to either a file, or just page and click RAEP. That's it. The program will now make 9001 requests to the webserver for the URL that you provided and reply with either the URL or the 404 message. Either way, you put some strain on the server. Do that with 50 people and it's byebye webserver.
UDP/TCP FLOODING HOW-TO: Fill in the IP address of say.. the webserver of subeta.org (default IP), select the port you'd like to make requests on (default 80). Select the protocol you'd like to use (default TCP) and click RAEP!. Same story as above, except with UDP or TCP packets. USE TCP FOR MAXIMUM DAMAGE TO THE SERVER!
WHAT ARE BLOCKING? If you turn this option on, the program will block any other operation while it's sending out the datapacket and waiting for a response for the server. While you're ensuring a response from the server, this can be very annoying on slow connections, but it forces the server to respond. Turn this off if you experience some lag in the sending or when the program freezes and dies. This can be noticed very well when selecting TCP as your protocol. Use TCP for ultimate bandwidth leeching.
FOR LONGCAT! FOR ANONYMOUS! WE ARE LEGION!
